   "source": [
    "# Agentic RAG evaluation demo (Google Colab)\n",
    "\n",
    "**End-to-end demo:** clone → download datasets (FinQA + TAT-QA) → build FinQA index on GPU → run RAG eval → display results.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Before running:** Runtime → Change runtime type → **T4 GPU**. Add `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in Colab Secrets (see section 5)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## What “agentic” RAG means here (loose definition)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Strict definition** of “agentic” = systems that act fully autonomously with no human in the loop. Many workplaces still require **human sign-off** on agent outputs, so job descriptions often use **“agentic RAG”** in a looser sense.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Loose definition (this repo):**\n",
    "- The RAG pipeline is **orchestrated**: it plans steps (e.g. “retrieve → then answer”), chooses tools (retrieval vs calculator), and can reflect or retry.\n",
    "- It is **multi-step** and **tool-using**: retrieval, optional reranking, then generation with access to retrieved context and optionally a calculator.\n",
    "- It is **not** fully autonomous: we run it in a controlled eval setting; in production, humans would verify and approve outputs.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Compared to “normal” RAG:**\n",
    "- **Normal RAG:** single shot — embed query → retrieve chunks → generate answer.\n",
    "- **This agentic RAG:** plan → retrieve (with optional corpus scoping, e.g. FinQA doc id) → optional rerank → generate with program-style hints and post-execution of numerical expressions — so the model can “use tools” and multi-step reasoning while still being human-in-the-loop."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Clone repo and install dependencies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "REPO_URL = \"https://github.com/leemingloon/ocr-agentic-rag.git\"\n",
    "REPO_DIR = \"ocr-agentic-rag\"\n",
    "import os\n",
    "os.environ[\"COLAB_GPU\"] = os.environ.get(\"COLAB_GPU\", \"1\")\n",
    "if os.path.isdir(REPO_DIR):\n",
    "    get_ipython().run_line_magic('cd', REPO_DIR)\n",
    "    get_ipython().system('git pull')\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    get_ipython().system(f'git clone {REPO_URL} {REPO_DIR}')\n",
    "get_ipython().run_line_magic('cd', REPO_DIR)\n",
    "\n",
    "!pip install -q sentence-transformers faiss-cpu rank_bm25 llama-index-core anthropic langgraph pandas"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Download RAG datasets (FinQA + TAT-QA)\n",
    "\n",
    "No manual upload. To download only one: `!python scripts/download_rag_datasets.py --datasets finqa`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!python scripts/download_rag_datasets.py --datasets finqa tatqa"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Generate first_5_rows for FinQA (optional)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import json\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "train_dir = Path(\"data/rag/FinQA/train\")\n",
    "train_qa_path = train_dir / \"train_qa.json\"\n",
    "first_5_path = train_dir / \"first_5_rows.json\"\n",
    "if train_qa_path.exists():\n",
    "    with open(train_qa_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n",
    "        data = json.load(f)\n",
    "    if isinstance(data, dict) and \"data\" in data:\n",
    "        data = data[\"data\"]\n",
    "    rows = data[:5] if isinstance(data, list) else []\n",
    "    with open(first_5_path, \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n",
    "        json.dump(rows, f, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)\n",
    "    print(f"Wrote {first_5_path} ({len(rows)} rows).\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"train_qa.json not found; run section 2 first.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Build FinQA retriever index (GPU on Colab)\n",
    "\n",
    "Uses GPU when available (Colab T4). On local CPU, omit `--batch_size` or use `--cpu`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "use_gpu = os.environ.get(\"COLAB_GPU\", \"1\") == \"1\"\n",
    "if use_gpu:\n",
    "    !python scripts/build_finqa_embeddings_colab.py --output data/rag/FinQA/train/finqa_retriever_index --batch_size 256\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    !python scripts/build_finqa_embeddings_colab.py --output data/rag/FinQA/train/finqa_retriever_index --cpu"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
